args: What do you have there, Albert?
A letter from a fellow Knight of Levin.
You keep in touch through letters?
That's right. Once I let them know my\nwhereabouts, they send them regularly.
Sounds like they're a good bunch.
They are better than I deserve.
So what does the letter say?
I have only just opened it. Let me see...
What's wrong? I don't think I've ever\nseen you look so surprised.
It seems one of the knights\nlearned where he is hiding.
Yes. It is time to end this.
My former friend is nothing to be trifled\nwith. Your life will be in danger.
Which is why I can't let you go alone.
We promised to aid you in your fight,\ndid we not?
...Ho there! We have come.\nIs everyone well?
Yes, sir—although we still haven't\nmade contact with the enemy.
But he's here. We're sure of it.
Then it's time to enter after him.\nStay on your guard.
He must have realized we were on to\nhim and escaped. Fie and fie again!
It looks as if someone was here recently.
We may have only missed him\nby a matter of minutes.
Actually, what IS this place? And why\nare there old books scattered around?
I imagine Yurius was using it\nfor his experiments.
Damn you, Yurius... What are you\nplanning to do with that seed...?
That cunning devil! He didn't just flee,\nhe left a trap behind!
That was the last of them.
But I fear this turned out to be\na waste of our time.
So long as everyone's all right,\nthat's all that matters.
It's too bad we missed Yurius, though.\nThis was our perfect chance.
Yet much as I hate to admit it,\nI feel...relief.
Relief I don't have to fight him.
Are you SURE about this plan\nof yours, Albert?
I mean, this guy's still your friend,\neven if he is all fiend-y now.
The idea of you fighting him\nis just super sad.
Even if you're able to eradicate the seed\nby killing Yurius, you're just going to\nend up feeling guilty all over again.
Yet I cannot permit such a foul thing\nto exist in this world.
You said the seeds grow by\nabsorbing people, right?
Isn't there some way to destroy JUST\nthe seed and return Yurius to normal?
But no matter how many old texts I looked\nthrough, I found no such means.
Which means my only option\nis to slay Yurius.
If you can't find a way on your own,\nmaybe we can find one together!
Two heads are better than one, right?!\n...Well, unless they're both yours,\nwhich has gotta be SUPER awkward.
We'll help you however we can, Albert.
Of course. So long as even the slightest\nhope exists, we have to try.
Yes, I suppose you're right.\nThank you, {player_name}.
